# Vue Component Rules

## Script
- Always `<script setup lang="ts">` — no Options API, no `defineComponent`
- Props: use `defineProps<{}>()` with TypeScript generic, never runtime props object
- Emits: use `defineEmits<{}>()` with TypeScript generic
- Expose nothing unless explicitly needed via `defineExpose()`

## Template
- One root element per component (no fragments unless intentional)
- `v-for` always has `:key` — never index as key unless list is static and never reordered
- `v-if` and `v-for` never on the same element — wrap with `<template>` instead
- Use `<component :is="">` for dynamic components
- Prefer `v-bind` shorthand (`:`) and `v-on` shorthand (`@`)

## Styles
- Always `<style lang="scss" scoped>` — never unscoped unless it's a global layout file
- Use SCSS variables from `assets/styles/_variables.scss` for colors, spacing, fonts
- Class names: BEM (`.project-card__title`, `.project-card--featured`)
- No inline styles

## Naming
- Page components: `pages/index.vue`, `pages/projects/[slug].vue`
- Section components: `components/sections/HeroSection.vue`, `AboutSection.vue`
- UI components: `components/ui/BaseButton.vue`, `BaseCard.vue`, `BaseBadge.vue`
- Prefix generic UI components with `Base`

## Example component skeleton
```vue
<script setup lang="ts">
interface Props {
  title: string
  featured?: boolean
}

const props = defineProps<Props>()
</script>

<template>
  <div class="project-card" :class="{ 'project-card--featured': props.featured }">
    <h3 class="project-card__title">{{ props.title }}</h3>
  </div>
</template>

<style lang="scss" scoped>
.project-card {
  &__title { }
  &--featured { }
}
</style>
```
